   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>GROUP 5</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE CHAIN OF HUMAN LIFE Subject Two Hundred Forty-two THE FIRST LINK SIN Scripture: Rom 5:12 Man is born, raised, grown, and immersed in sin Give examples to prove the sinfulness of man s behavior Subject Two Hundred Forty-three THE SECOND LINK DEATH Scripture: Rom 5:12; 6:23; Ezek.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>18:4 Death comes from sin, and hence is joined to sin</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The more sin a man commits the faster he dies.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>There are four steps in death The spirit is dead, lacking any sense of morality, and without knowledge of God.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The body will die.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The soul will be cast into Hades.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>At the end of the world, the body, soul, and spirit will be reunited to be thrown into the lake of fire.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Man lives in death today</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>He is not living daily, but is dying daily.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Subject Two Hundred Forty-four THE THIRD LINK JUDGMENT Scripture: Heb 9:27; Rev 20:11-13 There is a coming judgment</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>All the iniquity and unrighteousness that a man commits in his lifetime cannot be erased merely by death.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>There will be a judgment.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>In His word God said that man will suffer His judgment The future judgment is after a man s death</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The death of a man is not his end, but the beginning of a second stage.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The future judgment will be according to man s deeds today The future judgment is altogether just and righteous</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>It will be the judgment before the great white throne.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Unless a man believes in the Lord Jesus today, in that judgment he will stand condemned Subject Two Hundred Forty-five THE FOURTH LINK HELL Scripture: Rev 20:15; 21:8 Hell as God s jail When someone commits a crime he is judged and then put into jail.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The universe is governed by God.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>When man transgresses the law of God, he must be put into God s jail.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>This universal jail is called hell.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Hell being the lake of fire In the future, after God has judged man, He will send all the sinners to the lake of fire.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The lake of fire is what we commonly know as hell.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Describe the pains and the torment in hell.</S>
   </TEXT>
